<h1>Problem 1166 - 2010 IMO, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(I\) be the incentre of triangle \(ABC\) and let \(\Gamma\) be its circumcircle.  Let the line \(AI\) intersect \(\Gamma\) again at \(D\).  Let \(E\) be a point on the arc \(BDC\) and \(F\) a point on the side \(BC\) such that \[\angle BAF = \angle CAE < \tfrac{1}{2} \angle BAC.\]  Finally, let \(G\) be the midpoint of the segment \(IF\).  Prove that the lines \(DG\) and \(EI\) intersect on \(\Gamma\).</p>
